<title>Time Segmented Journal DAO</title>
<h1>Time Segmented Journal DAO</h1>
<p>The Time Segmented Journal DAO is a DAO which keeps data for each day in a separate MDAO and Journal.</p>
<p>Directory structure under journals/: year/month/day (yyyy/mm/dd).<br/>Month and Day are not padded, so January is 1 rather than 01.</p>
<p>Date used for segmentation is taken from the argument object.<br/>
The date property defaults to <b>created</b> (CreatedAware Interface).</p>
<p>Each day data is loaded into it's own MDAO.</p>

<h2>CRUD Behaviour</h2>
<p>
<ul>
<li><b>put (create and update)</b>: apply to the original FObject date (when provided).</li>
<li><b>select</b>: if no predicate, then 'today' is used, otherwise date range from
predicate is used to calculate 'days' of interest. Appropriate day journals
are loaded (if not cached). And finally an OR is applied across selected
day MDAOs.</li>
<li><b>find</b>: attempt to find the id in current cache of MDAOs</li>
</ul>
</p>

<h2>EasyDAO Support</h2>
<p>This DAO will be used as the Journal if EasyDAO.journalType is set to <b>TIME_SEGMENTED_JOURNAL</b>.</p>
<p>Defaults for date PropertyInfo and Filename will be used.</p>
